abstract: Jockey Ryan Moore wins Royal Ascot for ninth time, beating postwar record held by Lester Piggott and Pat Eddery.
lead_paragraph: The English jockey Ryan Moore, 31, broke a postwar record when he claimed his ninth victory of this week’s Royal Ascot flat meeting in London.

headline.main: A Record Ninth Victory at Royal Ascot
